    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <div class="faq-section fade-in">
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="faq-container">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
            <h4>Who can participate in HOTS: Siege of Shadows?</h4>
            <div class="toggle-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>HOTS is open to all Egyptian high school students. Participants must be currently enrolled in a high school in Egypt. All team members must be from the same school.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
            <h4>Is there a registration fee?</h4>
            <div class="toggle-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>No, registration for HOTS is completely free of charge. However, places are limited, so early registration is recommended.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
            <h4>Can I participate individually?</h4>
            <div class="toggle-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>No, HOTS is a team competition. Each team must consist of 3-4 students from the same school. The competition is designed to encourage teamwork and collaboration.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
            <h4>What subjects does the competition cover?</h4>
            <div class="toggle-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>HOTS focuses on a multidisciplinary approach, covering science, mathematics, engineering, and critical thinking. The competition is designed to test higher-order thinking skills rather than rote memorization.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
            <h4>How are teams evaluated?</h4>
            <div class="toggle-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Teams are evaluated based on their problem-solving abilities, innovative thinking, scientific accuracy, teamwork, and presentation skills. The competition consists of multiple rounds, with each round focusing on different aspects of these skills.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
